://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> Firstly, when you hit pickpocket you get coins from only one pool. From personal experience it seems to me you then get all the coins from that pool before you get coins of any other type.<br>
<br>
Pickpocket takes 11-12 seconds to refresh, so I'd usually expect to get it off 3-4 times a fight at most if I was chain-pickpocketing.<br>
<br>
With a skill of 178, I'd be surprised if I managed to take even 10% of a mob's average coin in that time. Sure, sometimes I might get lucky and hit the plat pool first time ... other times I'd get nothing. Consider the average.<br>
<br>
I'd imagine any rogue fighting in LoIO would have a much lower skill, and so get rather less.<br>
<br>
Finally, all of the above is working on the assumption that we do actually take coin from the main loot pool ... whereas I have a feeling that VI changed that quite a while ago for this exact reason. Someone might want to dig through the patch archives.<br>
<br>
Either way, this is all bullshit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umaeri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maeri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/10/02 3:39:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> Last patch message I recall reading said rogues pickpocket from the existing loot on the mob. Can only get cash and non-MAGIC items (so they can get gems, spells). And can never get the last coin of each type on a mob. All your mobs seem to have 1pp 1gp 1sp and 1cp left on the corpse? Check the halfling's pockets. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uavissuprema.showPublicProfile?language=EN>avissuprema</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/11/02 8:42:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=35>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> Discussion is old and many threats about it on other boards. But this is EMarr and so I want to give my 2 coppers too:<br>
I dont like PP skill hows implemented. I wish there would be a message or at least a little chance of failure so others can see it. Reply to arguments:<br>
- &lt;Practice<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  PP isnt hard to raise. Practice it when fighting with friends who trust you. At least ask if others mind you PPing. Using macro you can PP fast while fighting or even running/kiting. Or practise when alone on mobs near zone, so you have chance to run if you catched.<br>
- &lt;Group members see it when less cash on mob<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  No they cannot. They can guess, but not sure. Thats why loot message was implemented after 1 year EQ. And some mobs have no cash anyway.<br>
- &lt;Loot is only little cash and no magic items<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I did PP a spell while kiting with a friend in Skyfire. Sold it for 13k...<br>
- &lt;Roleplay<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Its no roleplay when group members cannot even see graphics when you put your hand on mobs belt. And from roleplay point of view a thief does solo jobs. But in EQ rogue is one of worst solo players. Even some greens can kick high lev rogues. EQ Rogues NEED groups, and I am sorry we have the skill to betray the group.<br>
- &lt;Its rogues special way to make money like porters and rezzers<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Stop whining. There are many other classes that cannot port or rez or have any special skill to earn some extra cash. And others do a trade, rogue gets it while ripping of his group, his partners.<br>
<br>
Hope I didnt forget a fat pro-PP argument. Have a nice day.<br>
<br>
Avis Suprema, Divine Grace <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulechevalierblanc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Le Chevalier Blanc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 3:16:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> My personal opinions and a few facts (I apologize if they were already brought up)<br>
<br>
a) PickPocket works on green mobs - that means you can practice pickpocket on an orc pawn and you will see skill advancements.  The excuse of &quot;I need to practice&quot; is weak and intolerable.<br>
<br>
b) A message is displayed by &quot;talking&quot; mobs - these are the mobs that say things when taunted also.  If a rogue fails his pickpocket attempt, there's a chance the mob will say &quot;Stop Thief!! &lt;roguename&gt;&quot;.  If you see this, it's a 100% sign that the rogue is pickpocketing.<br>
<br>
c) PickPocket does not work on undead.  It also doesn't work on most animals.  Basically, the mob has to be coded with &quot;pockets&quot; for PickPocket to work.<br>
<br>
d) There is a mob level cap of 48 for PickPocket to work for those rogues up to rogue level 53.  After level 53, you can PickPocket a mob 5 levels below your current level to a maximum of level 55 mobs when the rogue is level 60.<br>
<br>
e) To quell any confusion, there is only *one* loot pool on a mob.  Rogues steal from the one and only loot pool.  There are no &quot;seconday loot pools&quot; for rogues to steal from that don't affect the party.<br>
<br>
f) Any rogue that thinks that the minimal amount of cash or items obtained through PickPocketing is worth the reputation tarnish when caught... is deluded.<br>
<br>
g) Roleplaying is not an excuse for rude behavior.  If you think you can PickPocket from a group without informing them under the idea of &quot;roleplaying&quot;, then the cleric can choose not to heal you due to &quot;religious differences&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
h) The statement of &quot;It's our way to make money&quot; as an excuse to pickpocket in groups is just stupid.  If you're going to make extra money - do it on mobs that no one has engaged.  I, for example, pickpocket merchants since no-one will ever get exp or loot from them.  I'll sometimes do a &quot;drive-by&quot; pickpocket on a hill giant or sand giant that no-one has engaged.  You do not have to pickpocket in groups to gain any of the &quot;rewards&quot; for having the skill.<br>
<br>
<br>
Bottom line: It is just downright inconsiderate to pickpocket in groups without asking.  Rogues that pickpocket in a group are the same personality types that play KS'ing druids/wizards and camp stealing Necros.  One immature jerk tarnishes the perception of the entire class.  If you do it - you're just an asshole.  Don't try to hide behind any excuses...<br>
<br>
But that's just my opinion, I could be wrong... ([c] Dennis Miller)<br>
